----------------------------
DTL allows developers to separate the visual presentation of a site from the underlying code.
Syntax:
DTL uses tags ({% ... %}) for logic and variables ({{ ... }}) to display data.
Context:
Templates are rendered with a context, which is a dictionary of data passed from the Django view.
{% if condition %}
{% endif %}
{% else %}
{% for i in iterable %}
{% endfor %}
{% csrf_token %}
{% load static %}



how to load images on to UI page
SETTINGS : STATICFILES_DIRS = [
    os.path.join(BASE_DIR,'static')
]

{% load static %}


